  "texts": [
    "Recall that the set of proper filters in F b is the domain of (F b) g, andP g = { X | X ∈ F b } is the set of admissible sets in (F b) g, where X is the set of proper filters in F b that contain X.",
    "Let ⊑ ′ and R ′ i be the refinement and accessibility relations in (F b) g.For part 1, for every x ∈ S, P (x) is a proper filter in F b, so η F is indeed a map from F to (F b) g.For ⊑-matching, we must show that for all x ∈ S and all X ∈ P g,↓ ′ η F (x) ∩ X = ∅ iff ↓x ∩ η -1 F [ X] = ∅.",
    "From left-to-right, suppose there is a y ∈ ↓x ∩ η -1 F [ X], which means y ⊑ x and P (y) ∈ X.",
    "Since y ⊑ x, we have P (y) ⊇ P (x) by persistence.",
    "Thus, η F (y) ∈ ↓ ′ η F (x)∩ X. Conversely, suppose there is a proper filter F ∈ ↓ ′ η F (x) ∩ X, which means F ⊇ P (x) and X ∈ F. Then ¬X ̸ ∈ P (x), so x ̸ ∈ ¬X, which implies that there is a y ⊑ x such that y ∈ X, so X ∈ P (y) and hence P (y) ∈ X."
